 | product/productId: 6300215512 | review/userId: A1SDPA1J98UP4L | review/summary: Where Do Faded Hollywood Doves Go To Die? | review/text: Sunset Boulevard answers the age old question, Where Do Faded Hollywood Doves Go To Die? in truly greusome detail as we meet one Miss Norma Desmond.  Technically this is my most favorite picture of all time.  Norma Desmond is one truly twisted sister a fictional old film star now past it yet looking for her come back.  The movies are in her old tired blood and she seeks a close up like a heroin addict hunts for their next drug fix.  Norma Desmond courts that most elusive prey called youth and let me tell you this film chronicles the hunt which is driving her and all who surround her quite and quietly mad.<br /><br />Norma is yet another aging former star, a victim of that all too real Hollywood malady of beleiving her own press,  Norma in her heyday sowed the wind in treating people like dirt and reaped the worldwind as Hollywood disgarded her like yesterdays news when the wrinkles showed up and the glamour wore off.  Gloria Swanson was excellent as Norma Desmond because she was old enough to remember silent pictures and she had the exzagerated hand gesticulations and facial contortions used in the silent move era to convey feelings in a time before Talkies.<br /><br />Again if what I shared with you thus far was all there was to this movie it would be fun to watch but oh no.  Norma Desmond not only wants to re-energize her dead film career she wants a boy toy to replace the now dead monkey and friend she lives with in her faded dusty mansion that looks like a cross between a haunted house set, mad house and a large dusty tomb.  The film has an extra creepy feel as at the beginning you learn it is a story noir being told to you by a man now very dead.  Yes this is a story told by the dead victim of an explosive mixture of two demeanted peoples poison dreams and their immoral selfish willingness to do any wicked thing to make them come true.<br /><br />What makes Sunset Boulevard so good is that it feels so right.  Norma Desmond is such a man hungry self absorbed old babe and what started out as her lover's iron sense of dignity turns slowly into cotton candy norma consumes with a jaded passion.  Norma with all the deliberate cunning of a black widow spider slowly injects her lover with the potent venom of co-dependency which litterally eat away the kept man's backbone till he yields to her every whim for a time.  Helping Sunset Bolevard develop and keep its horrific mood is also the creepy music score which you can hear become more demented and manic as the characters lives and dignity self destruct as their tormented souls entertwine beyond hope of ever escaping each others perverse deadly embrace.<br /><br />There is plenty of dark humor in this Norma Desmonds Sunset Boulevard.  If this is a horror movie it is traggic horror.  Sunset Boulevard is certainly Psychological horror showing what twisted shallow minded people do to themselves and each other if their lusts for money, power and fame are unleashed by the proper situations.  Watching this movie is like watching to two animals eat each other alive while you the audience are enticed to take bets on which one will survive in the end.<br /><br />Finally this movie has a few mwmoriable lines too.  Her Lover says, ... "Hey You're Norma Desmond, You used to be BIG!"... To which Norma responds... I AM BIG its the picturh's that got small. and my favorite saying of all movies I have seen in life Norma's Desmonds swan song to the Camera's.<br /><br />"This is my life.  It always will be... There's no one else just us, the camera's and all those wonderful people out there in the dark..... Alright Mr DeMille I'm ready for my close up!".<br /><br />This is another of my must have DVD's.  Sunset Boulevard is serious in a weird way but in another way it is a solid black comedy laugh fest.  You have to buy Sunset Boulevard not to buy this is to cheat yourself of laughs galore.  Oh after seeing Sunset Bolevard you won't go swimming at any of Norma Desmonds Hollywood Parties unless you need to learn how to float.  I am sure if you are a young man willing to help write Norma a sure fire career reviving come back script she will gladly give you the crash course on floating in her pool.<br /><br />Play your cards right she might take you for a ride in her dusty old car.
