rd a yacht, and a mix of serious themes including abuse, alcoholism, unemployment, and murder among others.<p>The non-stop action, slapstick and reminiscent one-liners encouraged critics and movie goers alike to compare Widler's film to Marx Brothers classics, especially in the slapstick chases as gangsters pursue the heroes through hotel corridors.
