 | product/productId: 6300988805 | review/userId: A2ZHH7AK83JB5G | review/summary: Changed from the book but still worth seeing! | review/text: The characters of Charles Dickens's timeless tale come to life in spellbinding black and white that perfectly captures the book's tone.  Both Estella and Miss Havisham's characters are vastly sweetened from the book.  Estella has genuine affection for Pip instead of just seeing him as another person to manipulate.  Miss Havisham is actually concerned when Estella and Pip fight instead of being happy that her master plan of having Estella break Pip's heart is succeeding.  These changes allow for the overly saccharin ending that is greatly different in tone and plot from either of the two grim endings Dickens actually wrote for the book.
