 | product/productId: 079215827X | review/userId: A31T01WOZWV9YT | review/summary: GET READY FOR ADVENTURE | review/text: What can I say about the Indiana Jones movies that hasn't already been said a thousand times?  To me, they are the cornerstone of what a good adventure movie should be.  Suspenseful, humorous, exiting.  Great characters that touch your heart, raise your spirits and fire your blood.  What more can you ask for?<br /><br />I don't know if I should be the one to recap the trilogy.  As I'm sure many others have done, far better than I can.  But, on the off chance no one has, I'll give it a go.<br /><br />RAIDERS OF THE LOST ARK<br /><br />We meet the daring and intrepid archaeologist and adventurer, Indiana Jones, who is on the hunt for the legendary, Ark of the Covenant.  Jones must find the lost Ark before the Nazi's do.  Aided by ex-flame, Marion and site digger, Sallah, Jones manages to find the Ark, but not before the Nazi's find him.  It then becomes a game of keep-away between Jones and Belloq (rival archaeologist and Nazi tool).  Can Jones keep the Ark AND the girl?  Both of which he loses more than once.  Jones must brave fire, poison, a snake infested Egyptian tomb and a host of meddling Nazi's.  Will this adventure prove too daring for our hero?  (Since there are two more movies, it obviously doesn't.)  Will he recover the Ark?  And, more importantly, will he get the girl?<br /><br />THE TEMPLE OF DOOM<br /><br />This movie starts off with a bang.  After barely surviving poisoning, a nightclub brawl and a high-speed car chase through the streets of Shanghai, Indy is marooned in the jungles of India, along with pint-sized sidekick, Short Round and nightclub singer, Willie Scott (who proves to be more of a hindrance than a help).  They unwittingly stumble upon an ancient and evil cult that has enslaved the children of a local village.  Indy must free the children and brake the stronghold that the cult has in the area, without becoming a slave himself.<br /><br />Minor note.  Though this is the second installment in the trilogy, if you look at the dates given in the beginning of both Raiders and Temple of Doom, you'll notice that the Temple of Doom adventure preceded Raiders by a year.  That hardly matters in the grand scheme of things.  I just like pointing that out.<br /><br />THE LAST CRUSADE<br /><br />Indy's father has disappeared while on a quest for the Holy Grail.  A lifelong pursuit that has driven he and Indy apart.  Indy takes on the Grail search in an attempt to find clues leading to his fathers whereabouts.  Along the way he is lead to an Austrian castle where the Nazi's are holding Papa Jones in the hopes of finding the location of the Grail.  (CHEATERS!!!)  Indy and his father escape from the castle within an inch of their lives.  Now, they must elude capture while trying to make their way out of the country and head off the Germans before they can find the Grail.  Indy and his father must brave rat infested catacombs, German flying aces, a murderous tank and finally, a test of faith that will either lead them to the Grail or be the end of the Jones boys.<br /><br />I like these movies.  They're fun, adventuresome and entertaining.  Each movie stands on it's own. They just work.  The thing I like most about this box set is the fourth disc that contains bonus material for all three movies.  It shows you how they made each movie, what went into creating the character of Indiana Jones and the world he lives in.  Exciting!<br /><br />I think anyone would be pleased with this set.  There aren't three better movies out there.
