 | product/productId: 0800193873 | review/userId: A391RY3TA1MCVM | review/summary: Still fantastic after all these years | review/text: The Fifth Element was released in 1997 and is still far better than most movies released today, in large part because it is steeped in imagination and humour and gives new life to the old "The world is threatened, we need a hero to save us" storyline, even though this one features an embittered ex-soldier down on his luck. Rather than explain the film from start to finish I'd urge you to sit back and immerse yourself into some serious craziness. In parts the movie does descend into near incoherence yet saves itself each time with good humour and great acting, not to mention amazing backdrops and scenery design. The plot moves at a very rapid pace and several times while watching it again I had to hit the pause button and explain the latest twist to bemused relatives. The Ultimate Edition is particularly useful, since it offers a second DVD with a number of extra features on how the film was created and how the complex costumes were put together.
