 | product/productId: 079215827X | review/userId: A2WFNZWC8O6O1J | review/summary: Stays Just as Fun Now as Before! | review/text: INDIANA JONES is the ultimate action hero.  Superman doesn't compare.  Leave Jason Bourne at the door.  Sure, they're great and all, but Indy started it all.<br /><br />When I heard that all three INDIANA JONES movies were coming out on a trilogy three-pack, I was excited.  I had watched the films on old VHSs over and over, but I new I was going to have to replace them sometime.  This box set gave me the chance.<br /><br />The box set contains all three movies plus a bonus disc of special features.  The bonus disc doesn't exceed expectations but it very well meets them.  It includes a three-part documentary on all three films, featurettes, trailers, and DVD-rom features.<br /><br />The movies themselves:<br /><br />RAIDERS OF THE LOST ARK: It's a classic.  The whip.  The hat.  This movie was what made those two landmark props icons.  The film suceeds in all aspects of story, action, and climax.  The film is brilliantly scored by mastermind John Williams (of JAWS and STAR WARS fame).  The special effects at the climax aren't as realistic as, say, THE LORD OF THE RINGS movies, but one must remember that the film was made more than 20 years ago.<br /><br />THE TEMPLE OF DOOM:  Dark.  Action-packed.  Dark.  Scary.  And did I mention dark?  The second installment of the series is, by far, the darkest of the three.  In my opinion, some of the scenes in The Temple of Doom itself are unnessecary, and that whole Indy-recites-Hindu-spell thing towards the end of the film didn't quite work for me.  But the hilarious opening action scene ("Where's the diamond?") and the bridge sequence, not the mention the extraordinary mine car chase, make the film worth watching.  Just fast forward when you see the grinning madman reaching for a guy's chest.<br /><br />THE LAST CRUSADE: What can I say?  Rarely are two films in the trilogy classics.  RAIDERS and CRUSADE are the classics of this trilogy.  RAIDERS topped all of my charts, but I must say CRUSADE is my favorite Indy film thus far (I still have yet to see the fourth one, not yet released).  The touching storyline, intense action, and witty humor make this the best of the three films.  Sean Connery joins the brilliant cast as Indy's father, who is an archaeologist like his son, but has yet to adjust to the whole machine-gun thing.  This one's a must-see.<br /><br />Overall, this trilogy is well-worth buying.  This is, in my opinion, one of the best DVD trilogy boxsets out there, along with the original STAR WARS TRILOGY and BACK TO THE FUTURE.  All three films are good and the bonus disc doesn't disappoint.  Indy fans looking for a great buy, here's your chance.<br /><br />I just hope the fourth installment can live up to the milestone status that these three have created.<br /><br />Highly reccommended.
